Known Issue:

[2017_WW03 BKC][BIOS:118_R01][Neon city FPGA] P3V3 voltage on Purley-FPGA boards is 1.1V when system under S5 state 5345843

             it can be re-produced but no plan for the fixing. Details can be found 5345843 in HSD
  

P&P Update:

1. Changed CPU from B0 to H0 for power and performance test from WW04.

2. Run NLB with Linux kernel 4.7.0, other tests are running with Linux Kernel 3.10.0

3. Runing NLB GBS mode 0 lpbk1 to exercise 2 sockets simultaneously for NLB loading power test.

4. Target for all test items are not ready, But OSS need target to generate report, so we just use WW43\'s data as target.

5. FPGA power workload: NLB

6. Core performance workloads: Mlc, Linpack, Stream.

WW04:

a) No regression issue found, but the H0 CPU has higher power consumption and lower performance compared to the B0 CPU.

b) For power, the power consumption increased is caused by CPU changed.

    Changed CPU from QL66(B0 VIS) 235W 24Cores 1.7GHz to QM39(H0 VIS) 235W 24cores 2.1GHz

    The NLB loading test power consumption increased 5.94% (from 291.12W to 308.41W)-->HSD 5345865

c) For Performance, all these performance dropped are caused by CPU changed.

    Changed CPU from QLJ6(B0 VIS) 255W 28Cores 1.8GHz to QM38(H0 VIS) 255W 28cores 2.0GHz

    MP Linpack score dropped 6.47% (from 1453.7Gflops/s to 1359.6 Gflops/s)-->HSD 5345866

    MLC local idle memory latency increased 28.57% (from 65.8ns to 84.6ns)-->HSD 5345867

    MLC remote idle memory latency increased 9.25% (from 135.2ns to 147.7ns)-->HSD 5345868

Key Workaround (detail guide is here)

Pedigree and Board\nJumper Settings: guide

\n\n\n\n

Note: Only mandatory and necessary optional rework\nis implemented by BKC team

Mandatory rework FPGA JTAG chain missing CPU1 TCK resistor

Mandatory rework to replace FPGA KR RX AC Caps

Mandatory rework add a pull down to RSMRST

Mandatory rework to update VR FW

CPLD updates to address IFWI issue with 2 SKX FPGA\nCPUs populated

Required\nCPLD updates to address reset and FSC issues
